<small>'''Note <U+2160>:''' The symbol "'''O'''" represents whatever Hebrew letter is used.<br>
'''Note <U+2161>:''' The letter "'''[[<U+05E9>]]'''" is used since it can only be represented by that letter..<br>
'''Note <U+2162>:''' The dagesh, mappiq, and shuruk are different, however, they look the same and are inputted in the same manner.<br>
'''Note <U+2163>:''' The letter "'''[[<U+05D5>]]'''" is used since it can only be represented by that letter.</small>

